","text":"SBSDKGS1Handling"}],"abstract":[{"text":"GS1 message handling options.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The GS1 standard defines a key-value format for business-centric data that can be encoded into many 1D and 2D barcode types.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"https:\/\/ref.gs1.org\/standards\/genspecs\/","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkgs1handling","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGS1Handling"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGS1Handling","title":"SBSDKGS1Handling"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Allows to select the balance between result accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkoned